# Pem: SerpAPI engines + app cards (reference)

**Implementation:** `backend/src/integrations/serpapi.service.ts` (`fetchJson` → `https://serpapi.com/search.json`), **`backend/src/integrations/serpapi-query-parsers.ts`** (pipe formats for flights/hotels/reviews/ASIN/immersive token, **`deriveSerpRetryHint`**), and **`backend/src/agents/agent-tools/prep-google-bundle.ts`** (intent-aware `Promise.all` Serp + Tavily).

**Errors & retries:** SerpAPI often returns **HTTP 200** with `error` or `search_metadata.status: "Error"`. `fetchJson` treats those as failures and logs them. Engines that return **objects** (flights, hotels, trends, travel_explore, immersive_product, amazon_product, facebook_profile, maps_reviews) embed **`serp_error`** + **`serp_retry_hint`** in the JSON so the agent can fix the query and call `google()` again. Full engine list: [SerpAPI search engine APIs](https://serpapi.com/search-engine-apis).

**Types:** `GoogleVertical` in `prep-google-bundle.ts`. **`intentAllowsGoogleSerp`** includes `SHOPPING`, `RESEARCH`, `COMPARISON`, `DECISION`, `LEGAL_FINANCIAL`, `FIND_PLACE`, `FIND_PERSON`, `SCHEDULE_PREP`, `LIFE_ADMIN`.

## `google()` vertical → engine / method

| vertical | SerpAPI engine(s) | Service method | Notes |
|----------|-------------------|----------------|-------|
| `shopping` | `google_shopping` + `amazon` + Tavily | `googleShopping`, `amazonSearch`, shopping bundle | SHOPPING intent always this bundle |
| `local` | `google_local` | `googleLocal` | SMB / local pack style; also handles place/business searches (google_maps removed) |
| `local_services` | **`google_local`** (not Serp’s `google_local_services`) | `googleLocalServices` | Agent vertical name; implementation uses Maps local pack. SerpAPI’s **`google_local_services`** needs **`data_cid`** + allowlisted **`q`** (e.g. `electrician`) per [their docs](https://serpapi.com/google-local-services-api) — free-text “movers near X” returns HTTP 400. |
| `web` | `google` organic | `googleOrganic` | |
| `news` | `google_news` | `googleNewsEngine` | Dedicated news engine |
| `images` | `google_images` | `googleImages` | |
| `images_light` | `google_images_light` | `googleImagesLight` | Faster image search |
| `jobs` | `google_jobs` | `googleJobs` | |
| `finance` | `google_finance` | `googleFinance` | Tickers / instruments |
| `events` | `google_events` | `googleEvents` | Concerts, festivals; optional `htichips` via method opts (not exposed on tool yet) |
| `flights` | `google_flights` | `googleFlights` | Query **`flight\|DEP\|ARR\|YYYY-MM-DD`** |
| `hotels` | `google_hotels` | `googleHotels` | SerpAPI uses **`q`** + **`check_in_date`** / **`check_out_date`** ([docs](https://serpapi.com/google-hotels-api)). Parser: pipe **`hotel\|area or name\|YYYY-MM-DD\|YYYY-MM-DD`**, or any two ISO dates in free text, else defaults (+14d / 2-night) with full string as `q`. |
| `forums` | `google_forums` | `googleForums` | Discussions / forums |
| `maps_reviews` | `google_maps_reviews` | `googleMapsReviews` | Query **`reviews\|DATA_ID`** |
| `travel_explore` | `google_travel_explore` | `googleTravelExplore` | Trip inspiration |
| `trends` | `google_trends` | `googleTrends` | Keyword interest |
| `immersive_product` | `google_immersive_product` | `googleImmersiveProduct` | **`product\|PAGE_TOKEN`** from Shopping |
| `amazon_product` | `amazon_product` | `amazonProduct` | ASIN or **`asin\|B0…`** |
| `apple_app_store` | `apple_app_store` | `appleAppStore` | App search |
| `home_depot` | `home_depot` | `homeDepot` | Retail |
| `facebook_profile` | `facebook_profile` | `facebookProfile` | Public profile id — use responsibly |
| `scholar` | `google_scholar` | `googleScholar` | Academic (not Google Play) |

**Legacy helper:** `googleNews()` still uses `engine=google` + `tbm=nws` inside `serpapi.service.ts`; **`news` vertical uses `googleNewsEngine()`** (`engine=google_news`).

## Intent routing (high level)

- **FIND_PLACE:** default `maps`; also `events`, `local`, `local_services`, `travel_explore`, `maps_reviews` (see `executeGoogleBundle`).
- **LIFE_ADMIN:** `maps` or travel stack (`flights`, `hotels`, `travel_explore`, `events`, `local`, `local_services`, `finance`, `trends`) or falls back to web + Tavily.
- **RESEARCH / COMPARISON / DECISION:** full vertical set via `runResearchVerticalBundle`.
- **LEGAL_FINANCIAL:** `google()` enabled — prefer `finance`, `news`, `web`, `scholar`, `forums` + synthesis; never invent citations.

## App cards

Structured **Serp JSON** feeds the prep agent and the **adaptive formatter** (`RESEARCH_CARD`, `PLACE_CARD`, `SHOPPING_CARD`, etc.). There is **not** a separate Expo component per Serp engine today — new **dedicated card types** (e.g. events-only layout) are added when UX needs a distinct layout; extend **`PrepAdaptiveStack`** + Zod schema in the same change.

## Not wired (product direction)

| Engine | Notes |
|--------|--------|
| `google_videos` / YouTube | Prefer YouTube Data API for prod quotas |
| `walmart` / `ebay` / `bing_shopping` | Extra retail |
| `airbnb` / `zillow` | Vertical-specific |

## Expo / RN

- Prefer **`RemoteImageOrPlaceholder`** + **`normalizeRemoteImageUri`**; prefer **`serpapi_thumbnail`** when SerpAPI provides it (see **`pem-search-provider-routing.mdc`**).

## Env

- **`SERP_API_KEY`** — required for SerpAPI-backed bundles.
